pub struct Response<T> {
    pub context: RpcResponseContext,  // includes slot from bank
    pub value: T,
}
```

Helper function (lines 143-148 rpc.rs):
```rust
fn new_response<T>(bank: &Bank, value: T) -> RpcResponse<T> {
    RpcResponse {
        context: RpcResponseContext::new(bank.slot()),
        value,
    }
}
```

Common return types:
- `Result<RpcResponse<T>>` for methods returning context + value
- `Result<Vec<T>>` for array results without context
- `BoxFuture<Result<T>>` for async methods

